TopicTitle: [1.12.5] Bluedog Design Bureau - Stockalike Saturn, Apollo, and more! (v1.13.0 "Забытый" 13/Aug/2023)

Articles.Content: That's just the conditional that requires not having TAC LS installed to be active. TAC LS patches all fuel cells into being different modules, it would cause all sorts of b9 'missing module' errors if not handled with !TacLifeSupport (the '!' is 'not')

15 minutes ago, Rodger said:

That's just the conditional that requires not having TAC LS installed to be active. TAC LS patches all fuel cells into being different modules, it would cause all sorts of b9 'missing module' errors if not handled with !TacLifeSupport (the '!' is 'not')

6 hours ago, GoldForest said:

Yeah, deleting the water producing module did nothing. Hmmm... 

Looking at the log it says "!TacLifeSupport." 

I don't have Tac, does that have something to do with it? 

! in front of a Variable (in this Case TacLifeSupport   means **NOT** TacLifeSupport  AKA you only pass this variable check if you do not have TACLS.

Most commonly seen as != or "Not equal to"

1 hour ago, GoldForest said:

RPM is stopping the H/O fuel cell from working?.... That is weird... Got a fix for it? Besides deleting RPM?

Well, I just tried it with RPM and it worked fine too. I'd suggest at least updating RPM first to see if that fixes it https://github.com/FirstPersonKSP/RasterPropMonitor/releases - looks like the one you have is 2 minor patches old. However it looks like some other mod is also doing what RPM did instead, causing the same bug.

Another option to try is to save the craft after switching to H/O, then re-loading it. Failing that you could make a patch to just set H/O to be the default option for these fuel cells.

by the end of the year

Thanks to that Scourge probe we got enough budget for the next mission.

Mission: Manned Flyby of Windswept.

Payload: Gemini Spacecraft named Beaufort (Cookie for name reference).

Crew: Valentina and Bill.

Launch Vehicle: Saturn V with a Centaur.

The rest of the launch.

Spoiler

I even remembered to turn of the center engine halfway or so.

After we got into Frontier orbit we waited for our time and went for it

After a long time cramped in a ship the size of a VW our crew entered Windswept's SOI and unlike the unmanned test we kept the S-IV stage on due to almost running out of fuel in the test (It paid off big time.)

Val became the first Kerbal to EVA out above a different planet and it was broadcasted live.

Unfortunately Val's EVA was short lived due to the flyby was half day and half night.

One last shot of Bill checking the panels before dark.

After more another enduring trip we made it back to Frontier.

Reentry wasn't bad only sustained about.....14G. Atleast we didn't burn up ^^;

Overall the Saturn V technically has more than enough Delta V but given my skills and patience even with Mechjeb I tend to use alot lol.

Apollo and Big G have a meetup.

Full album: Imgur: The magic of the Internet

On 5/19/2024 at 5:28 AM, GuyWhoEnjoysFlyingThings said:

Hello. I hate building rockets, and I suck. Someone told me there were pre made rockets, but I don't see them. Where can I find these? Thanks

Hello and welcome, well, just install the mod and build your own. Here's the link to the wiki made by Friznit where you can find all the build guides for BDB's rockets which are made for planet packs with a 2.7x scale (like JNSQ or KSRSS).

In the wiki you'll have the instructions for making the most iconic rockets used by NASA.

Have fun.
